data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action<...>` signature means you can use normal C# control flow — no more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` gymnastics.

---

### 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full paths

Two related changes:

- **Same-named properties across complex types** (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get disambiguated column names (a number suffix is appended).
- **Nested complex types** now include the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both will generate rename migrations. To **keep existing column names**, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // ...other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types, preserve the old shorter column name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

After configuring, run `dotnet ef migrations add VerifyNoRenames` and confirm the migration is empty.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on the interface now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Update your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for safe logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same fix to every other method on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
